  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Procurement Specialist",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>·      Source and evaluate suppliers for transport services, warehouse-related items, office supplies, IT services, and other\noperational needs.​</p><p>·      Request, compare, and analyse quotations to\nensure competitive pricing and service levels.</p><p>·      Negotiate terms, prices, and contracts with vendors in line with company budget and quality requirements.​</p><p>·      Raise and manage orders, track deliveries, and ensure proper documentation and filing.​</p><p>·      Monitor supplier performance, address issues, and maintain good working relationships.</p><p>·      Coordinate with Operations, Finance, and Management to understand requirements and plan procurement activities.​</p><p>·      Support any procurement-related projects or initiatives assigned by Management.</p><p>Requirements</p><p>·     2–3 years of procurement or sourcing experience</p><p>·      Strong negotiation, coordination, and communication skills.</p><p>·     Proficient in MS Office (especially Excel)</p><p>·     Meticulous, organised, and able to work independently in a fast-paced environment.</p>",
